455
00:45:35,396 --> 00:45:36,437
Six.
Six?

456
00:45:36,605 --> 00:45:38,687
It's that lace that fooled you.
I say three.

457
00:45:38,855 --> 00:45:42,646
Watch him. I hear Cleve's an expert on
petticoats. Anyway, you can never prove it.

458
00:45:42,814 --> 00:45:44,856
We're going to be late
for that poker game.

459
00:45:45,023 --> 00:45:47,814
Look. I've just stuck you
for the most expensive dinner in St. Louis.

460
00:45:47,982 --> 00:45:50,053
I don't mind sticking
you a bit deeper. I'll

461
00:45:50,084 --> 00:45:51,970
I lay you a hundred it's
no less than six.

462
00:45:52,108 --> 00:45:54,441
How will you prove it?
Go backstage and find out.

463
00:45:54,609 --> 00:45:58,067
If I go back and check with you.
Fair enough.

464
00:46:05,320 --> 00:46:07,277
Second girl.

465
00:46:10,613 --> 00:46:12,653
Miss Prescott? Miss Prescott?
later.

466
00:46:12,821 --> 00:46:15,154
It's rather important.

467
00:46:15,322 --> 00:46:16,905
It's always important.

468
00:46:17,073 --> 00:46:19,655
The older they are.
the more important it gets.

469
00:46:19,823 --> 00:46:22,406
Miss Prescott, please.
I an Hylan Seabury...

470
00:46:22,573 --> 00:46:25,656
...attormey in the matter
of Jonathan Brooks.

471
00:46:25,949 --> 00:46:27,823
He means nothing to you?

472
00:46:27,991 --> 00:46:29,282
That old goat?

473
00:46:29,450 --> 00:46:32,075
Well, you must've meant
something to him, Miss Prescott.

474
00:46:32,242 --> 00:46:33,992
